# JavaScript Practice in Exercises for Programmers

## Challenge 1 - Saying Hello

### Pseudocode

Initialize name
Initialize greetingMessage

Prompt for name with "What is your name?"

Concatentate name into greetingMessage "Hello name, nice to meet you!"

Display updated greetingMessage that includes name


## Challenge 2 - Counting the Number of Characters

### Pseudocode

Initialize inputString
Initialize charCount

Prompt for inputString with "What is the input string?"

Count characters for inputString using built-in function

Display message with inputString and charCount - "inputString has charCount characters."


## Challenge 3 - Printing Quotes

### Inputs
quoteString
authorName

### Outputs
finalMessage

### Pseudocode
Prompt for quoteString with "What is the quote?"
Prompt for authorName with "Who said it?"

Contatenate finalMessage with "authorName says, "quoteString."" (using escape characters)

Display finalMessage


## Challenge 4 - Mad Lib

### Inputs
inputNoun
inputVerb
inputAdverb
inputAdjective

### Outputs
finalMessage

### Pseudocode
Prompt for inputNoun with "Enter a noun:"
Prompt for inputVerb with "Enter a verb:"
Prompt for inputAdverb with "Enter a adverb:"
Prompt for inputAdjective with "Enter a adjective:"

Contatenate finalMessage with "Do you inputVerb your inputAdjective inputNoun inputAdjective? That's hilarious!"

Display finalMessage


